
  ADDING NEW TASKS

  Adding another task, e.g. istream.c to a host requires modifications to:-

   -  Makefile
        LIB_OBJS = msg.o \
                   ...
                   istream.o \
                   ...

   -  main.c

        ...
        #include "net/istream.h"
        ...
        static const MsgProc __flash proctab[] = {
            ...
            [ISTREAM] = receive_istream,
            ...
        };
        ...

   -  host.h

        ...
        typedef enum {
            ...
            ISTREAM,
            ...
        } __attribute__ ((packed)) ProcNumber;
        ...

  istream.c is a network secretary which requires dynamic initialization:-

   -  sysinit.c

        ...
        static const ProcNumber __flash inittab[] = {
            ...
            ISTREAM,
            ...
        };
        ...

  If it needs control input inp.c may need to be modified.

  If the task declares a pre-start init function this should be called from
  within main.c in the pre-start init section.
